<h3>Prioritization</h3>
<div class="subFeatures">
    <div class="post">
        <h4>Optimization: GPU based skinning</h4>
        <div class="votes">
            <div class="voteControl">
                <a class="upVote" href="#"><i class="icon-chevron-up"></i></a>
                <div><strong>1203</strong><span>votes</span></div>
                <a class="downVote" href="#"><i class="icon-chevron-down"></i></a>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="poster">
            <div class="avatar">
                <img src="/img/placeholders/avatar-11.jpeg" />
            </div>
            <div class="name">Dan Dobbs</div>
        </div>
        <div class="details">
            <div>I have a game with many animated characters and the performance suffers quite a bit due to the skeletal animation processing happening CPU side. If the heavy math was offloaded to the fast GPUs (where supported) it would greatly speedup my game and let the players enjoy a nice high framerate even with a full battlefield!</div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="post">
        <h4>Animation Splitting</h4>
        <div class="votes">
            <div class="voteControl">
                <a class="upVote" href="#"><i class="icon-chevron-up"></i></a>
                <div><strong>754</strong><span>votes</span></div>
                <a class="downVote" href="#"><i class="icon-chevron-down"></i></a>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="poster">
            <div class="avatar">
                <img src="/img/placeholders/avatar-12.png" />
            </div>
            <div class="name">Jacky Chan</div>
        </div>
        <div class="details">
            <div>
                I have a bunch of characters with animations all in one FBX file, so when importing into the engine I need to be able to split the animations using a separate XML file which defines the animation names and keyframe ranges. The tangents at the start and end frames need to be repaired in order to allow seemless looping!
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<h3>Idea Lab</h3>
<div class="subFeatures">
